The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 June is 43,451 (5,029.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 June, there were 475 new confirmed cases (55.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 June, there were 278 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 71% (197 extra cases).
